            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Ceithernach</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary"> 
                <list type="witDetail">
                    <item n="1"><p><hi rend="italic">Ceithernach</hi> 'member or leader of a <hi rend="italic">ceithern</hi>'; <hi rend="italic">ceithern</hi> 'a band of fighting-men' (<ref source="https://dil.ie/8534">eDIL</ref>). Attested as a personal name in the annals from the 8th to the 13th centuries (<ref source="https://medievalscotland.org/kmo/AnnalsIndex/Masculine/Ceithernach.shtml">Index of Names in Irish Annals</ref>), including the obit in 773 of 'Ceithernach h-ua Erumono, abbas Cluana Ferta Brenaind' (abbot of Clonfert, Co. Galway).</p></item> 
                       </list>
